choices.text:
ammo availability. I did not want to stock up too much on ammo before moving to Michigan, as this means that I will have to worry about ammo logistics when driving 1,000’s of miles away from home, or when i have to transport the ammo through different jurisdictions.

But the hard part is, stores aren’t likely to have what I need now, and might not have anything in the future.

For example, around early June, the gun store I used to buy my ammo from claimed that they had 1,000 rounds of 9mm FMJ in stock, for a day before they sold out. The next day they called me up on the phone to tell me that they have ran out of stock and have not restocked on ammo anytime since then.

Cycles and Trends

In my limited experience here in Michigan, I don’t see cheap prices ever coming back again. Everything seems to be exploding, especially in the Ammo department.

Right now, I believe it’s an opportunity to buy ammo at cheap prices.

Long-term, it’s a big unknown. It’s a black-box (incredibly frustrating, but that’s what it seems like), and I don’t think anyone is able to really predict.

What To Do?

Action:

There’s not much we can do other than continuing to keep calm and carry on.
